HEADWORD: Detestation
<hw>Det`es*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>detestatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧testation</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of detesting; extreme hatred or dislike; abhorrence;
loathing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We are heartily agreed in our <qex>detestation</qex> of civil
war.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Detester</ent>⟦br⟧
